be.uantwerpen.fti.ds.sc.smartracecar.simdeployer

Class SimDeployer

  • java.lang.Object
    • be.uantwerpen.fti.ds.sc.smartracecar.simdeployer.SimDeployer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TCPListener

    class SimDeployer
extends java.lang.Object
implements TCPListener
    Module that handles all simulated vehicles and communicates with the SimWorker service to setup new simulated F1 cars. It deploys and manages the '.jar' versions of the vehicle simulation.

      • parseTCP

        public java.lang.String parseTCP(java.lang.String message)
                          throws java.io.IOException
        Interfaced method to parse TCP message socket callback is triggered by incoming message. Used to create, run , set, stop , kill or restart simulated vehicles by handling these incoming request from the SimWorker.
        Specified by:
        parseTCP in interface TCPListener
        Parameters:
        message - received TCP socket message string
        Returns:
        a return answer to be send back over the socket to the SimWorker. Here being ACK or NACK.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • createVehicle

        private boolean createVehicle(long simulationID)
        Called when a simulated vehicle needs to be created. This doesn't start the simulation yet but makes it ready in the backend systems and in the SimDeployer, ready to be altered and managed.
        Parameters:
        simulationID - The ID of the vehicle that needs to be created.
        Returns:
        A boolean to signify if the request could be handled or not. False means it could not be processed.

      • stopVehicle

        private boolean stopVehicle(long simulationID)
        Called when a simulated vehicle needs to be stopped. This doesn't remove the vehicle from the systems or ends the simulation. It simply disables the vehicle from receiving any jobs or requests and makes it hidden from the visualization. This allows it to be altered or restarted.
        Parameters:
        simulationID - The ID of the vehicle that needs to be stopped.
        Returns:
        A boolean to signify if the request could be handled or not. False means it could not be processed.

      • killVehicle

        private boolean killVehicle(long simulationID)
        Called when a simulated vehicle needs to be removed. This stops the simulation no matter what state it is in. It does request a unregistering from the backBone however through the simulated Core.
        Parameters:
        simulationID - The ID of the vehicle that needs to be killed.
        Returns:
        A boolean to signify if the request could be handled or not. False means it could not be processed.

      • restartVehicle

        private boolean restartVehicle(long simulationID)
        Called when a simulated vehicle needs to be restarted. This makes it restart at it's currently set startpoint and if the vehicle was stopped makes it available again for jobs and requests.
        Parameters:
        simulationID - The ID of the vehicle that needs to be restarted.
        Returns:
        A boolean to signify if the request could be handled or not. False means it could not be processed.

      • runVehicle

        private boolean runVehicle(long simulationID)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        Called when a simulated vehicle needs to be run. This makes it start the simulation(if it wasn't started already). If the vehicle was stopped then it simply unpauses it and makes it available again for jobs and requests. IF the vehicle wasn't run yet this will make the simulation actually start by launching the jars.
        Parameters:
        simulationID - The ID of the vehicle that needs to be restarted.
        Returns:
        A boolean to signify if the request could be handled or not. False means it could not be processed.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
